==English==

===Proper noun===
'''Jonathan'''
# A male [[given name]]. From [[Hebrew]] meaning "A gift from God".  The most famous Jonathan was [[King Saul]]'s son in the ancient [[Israel]].  He became best friends with the future King [[David]], son of [[Jessie]].
'''German'''
In [[German]], The name for Jonathan is Yonathan

